画像分類してみよう(仮)¶

Handwritten or MachinePrinted¶

※かなり特殊な独自のデータセットを使っているのでまだ一般的なデータセットでは使えません。¶

このノートブックは画像分類器を作る例です。成果物として入力された文字画像が手書き文字か機械が印字した文字か判定する分類器を作成します。
シンプルな例はMNISTなど素晴らしいものがたくさんあるのでここでは自作データセットを読み込んでみます。
データセットは下記の感じで用意しています。(1クラス1ディレクトリ)

  • 手書き文字：IAM databaseから取得した手書き文字画像から、word単位で切り出したもの
  • 印字文字　：上記wordの文字をフォントやサイズ・カラー(グレーだけど)をランダムに選択してPILで画像化したもの

※このノートブックはランタイムがTPUのColaboratoryで実行することを前提にしています。¶

※画像データセットはGoogle Driveに格納してある前提です。取得元は自由に書き換えてください。¶

Google Drive のマウント¶

下記を実行すると認証を求められるので、認証すればGoogle Driveがマウントされる。
その後データセットをコピーする。(wgetとかでパブリックなデータセットをとってきてもOK)

from IPython.display import Image,display_jpeg
from PIL import Image as PIL_Image

def load_IAMcliped_data():

    file_list = os.listdir(IMAGE_DIR)
    
    df = pd.DataFrame(file_list,columns=['img'])
    tmp_df = df['img'].str.split('_', expand=True)
    tmp_df.columns = ['filename', 'id']
    df['filename'] = tmp_df['filename'] + '.jpg'
    file_list = df['filename'].unique().tolist()
    
    train_list = random.sample(file_list,k=int(len(file_list)*0.9))
    test_list = list(set(file_list) - set(train_list))
    
    #さすがに全データ流し込めなかったので一部Drop
    
    train_list = random.sample(train_list,k=int(len(train_list) * KEEP_DATA_RATE))
    test_list = random.sample(test_list,k=int(len(test_list) * KEEP_DATA_RATE))
    
    train_df_handwritten = HANDWRITTEN_DIR +  df[df['filename'].isin(train_list)]
    test_df_handwritten = HANDWRITTEN_DIR + df[df['filename'].isin(test_list)]
    train_df_handwritten['Id'] = 'handwritten'
    train_df_handwritten['y_train'] = 0
    test_df_handwritten['AnswerId'] = 'handwritten'
    
    train_df_printed = PRINTED_DIR +  df[df['filename'].isin(train_list)]
    test_df_printed = PRINTED_DIR + df[df['filename'].isin(test_list)]
    train_df_printed['Id'] = 'printed'
    train_df_printed['y_train'] = 1
    test_df_printed['AnswerId'] = 'printed'
    
    train_df = pd.concat([train_df_handwritten, train_df_printed]).reset_index(drop=True)
    test_df = pd.concat([test_df_handwritten, test_df_printed]).reset_index(drop=True)
    
    train_df['Image'] = train_df['img']
    train_df = train_df.drop(columns='img')
    test_df['Image'] = test_df['img']
    test_df = test_df.drop(columns='img')
    
    train_df = train_df.sample(frac=1).reset_index(drop=True)
    test_df = test_df.sample(frac=1).reset_index(drop=True)
    
    train_df.to_csv('/content/work/debug/train.csv',header=True,index=False)
    test_df.to_csv('/content/work/debug/test.csv',header=True,index=False)
    
    
    x_train = prepareImages(train_df, train_df.shape[0])
    x_train /= 255

    y_train = train_df['y_train'].astype('int').drop(columns=list(set(train_df.columns) - set(['y_train']))).values
    if len(y_train.shape) == 1:
      y_train = y_train.reshape(y_train.shape[0],1)
    
    img_train, ann_train, img_val, ann_val = train_test_split(x_train, y_train, train_size=0.9, random_state=1)
    return img_train, img_val, ann_train, ann_val

def remove_background_color(img, dropout_level=200):
    img_np = np.array(img)
    mask_white = img_np > dropout_level
    img_np[mask_white] = 255
    img = PIL_Image.fromarray(img_np)
    return img
    
def prepareImages(data, m):
    print("Preparing images")
    X_train = np.zeros((m, IMAGE_SIZE, IMAGE_SIZE, 3))
    count = 0
    
    for fig in tqdm(data['Image']):
        #load images into images of size 100x100x3
        img = image.load_img(fig, target_size=(IMAGE_SIZE, IMAGE_SIZE, 3))
        # 背景色で学習している可能性があるので背景色削除
        remove_background_color(img)
        x = image.img_to_array(img)
        x = preprocess_input(x)

        X_train[count] = x
        count += 1
    
    return X_train

def prepare_labels(y):
    values = np.array(y)
    label_encoder = LabelEncoder()
    integer_encoded = label_encoder.fit_transform(values)
    #print(integer_encoded)

    onehot_encoder = OneHotEncoder(sparse=False)
    integer_encoded = integer_encoded.reshape(len(integer_encoded), 1)
    onehot_encoded = onehot_encoder.fit_transform(integer_encoded)
    # print(onehot_encoded)

    y = onehot_encoded
    # print(y.shape)
    return y, label_encoder
  
def check_results(cpu_model):
    test_images = pd.read_csv('/content/work/debug/test.csv')
    test_images_sample = test_images.sample(15).reset_index(drop=True)

    test_sample = prepareImages(test_images_sample, test_images_sample.shape[0])
    test_sample = test_sample / 255
    predictions_sample = cpu_model.predict(test_sample, verbose=1)
    test_result_df_sample = pd.DataFrame(predictions_sample, columns=['handwritten', 'machine_printed'])
    test_result_df_sample['filename'] = test_images_sample['Image']
    for data in test_result_df_sample.values.tolist():
      print('*********************************************')
      display_jpeg(Image(data[2]))
      print(data[2])
      print('handwritten :' + str(data[0]) + '     ' + 'machine :' + str(data[1]))
    
    test = prepareImages(test_images, test_images.shape[0])
    test = test / 255
    predictions = cpu_model.predict(test, verbose=1)
    test_result_df = pd.DataFrame(predictions, columns=['handwritten', 'machine_printed'])
    test_result_df['filename'] = test_images['Image']
    precision, recall = eval_results(test_result_df)
    return precision, recall

def eval_results(df):
    cliped_df = df[df['filename'].str.contains('cliped_images')]
    created_df = df[df['filename'].str.contains('created_images')]
    TP_df = pd.concat([cliped_df[cliped_df['handwritten'] >= 0.5], created_df[created_df['machine_printed'] >= 0.5]])
    FN_df = pd.concat([cliped_df[cliped_df['handwritten'] < 0.5], created_df[created_df['machine_printed'] < 0.5]])
    FP_df = pd.concat([created_df[created_df['handwritten'] >= 0.5], cliped_df[cliped_df['machine_printed'] >= 0.5]])
    TN_df = pd.concat([created_df[created_df['handwritten'] < 0.5], cliped_df[cliped_df['machine_printed'] < 0.5]])
    precision = len(TP_df) / (len(TP_df) + len(FP_df))
    recall = len(TP_df) / (len(TP_df) + len(FN_df))
    return precision, recall

def create_normal_model():
    model = VGG16(include_top=False, input_shape=(IMAGE_SIZE,IMAGE_SIZE,3), weights="imagenet")
    x = GlobalAveragePooling2D()(model.layers[-1].output)
    x = Dense(CLASS_COUNT, activation="softmax")(x)
    # あとでBatchNormを入れるため係数の固定はしない。初期値設定のみ転移学習とする
    return Model(model.inputs, x)

def create_batch_norm_model():
    model = create_normal_model()
    for i, layer in enumerate(model.layers):
        if i==0:
            input = layer.input
            x = input
        else:
            if "conv" in layer.name:
                layer.activation = activations.linear
                x = layer(x)
                x = BatchNormalization()(x)
                x = Activation("relu")(x)
            else:
                x = layer(x)

    bn_model = Model(input, x)
    return bn_model

def generator(X, y, batch_size):
    # 32->64に引き伸ばす操作でメモリ食い過ぎるので自分でジェネレーター書く
    while True:
        indices = np.arange(X.shape[0])
        np.random.shuffle(indices)
        if X.shape[1] < 48:
            for i in range(X.shape[0]//batch_size):
                current_indices = indices[i*batch_size:(i+1)*batch_size]
                X_batch = X[current_indices]
                # 2倍に引き伸ばす
                X_batch = X_batch.repeat(2, axis=1).repeat(2, axis=2)
                X_batch = X_batch / 255.0
                y_batch = to_categorical(y[current_indices], CLASS_COUNT)
                yield X_batch, y_batch
        else:
            for i in range(X.shape[0]//batch_size):
                current_indices = indices[i*batch_size:(i+1)*batch_size]
                X_batch = X[current_indices]
                y_batch = to_categorical(y[current_indices], CLASS_COUNT)
                yield X_batch, y_batch

def train(use_batch_norm):
#     (X_train, y_train), (X_test, y_test) = cifar10.load_data()
    X_train, y_train, X_test, y_test = load_IAMcliped_data()

    if use_batch_norm:
        model = create_batch_norm_model()
    else:
        model = create_normal_model()

    # 元の係数を壊さないように低めの学習率を使う
    model.compile(tf.train.RMSPropOptimizer(4e-6), "categorical_crossentropy", ["acc"])
    model.summary()

    tpu_grpc_url = "grpc://"+os.environ["COLAB_TPU_ADDR"]
    tpu_cluster_resolver = tf.contrib.cluster_resolver.TPUClusterResolver(tpu_grpc_url)
    strategy = keras_support.TPUDistributionStrategy(tpu_cluster_resolver)
    model = tf.contrib.tpu.keras_to_tpu_model(model, strategy=strategy)

#     hist = History()
    best_save_model_file = '/content/work/mymodel.h5'
    history = History()
    callbacks = [
                 EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss',
                               patience=20,
                               verbose=1,
                               min_delta=0.00001,
                               mode='min'),
    #              ReduceLROnPlateau(monitor='val_loss',
    #                                factor=0.1,
    #                                patience=2,
    #                                verbose=1,
    #                                min_delta=0.0001,
    #                                mode='min'),
                 ModelCheckpoint(monitor='val_loss',save_weights_only=True,
                                 filepath=best_save_model_file,
                                 save_best_only=True,
                                 mode='min') ,
                 history,
                 ]


    batch_size = BATCH_SIZE

    model.fit_generator(generator(X_train, y_train, batch_size), steps_per_epoch=X_train.shape[0]//batch_size,
                        validation_data=generator(X_test, y_test, batch_size), 
                        validation_steps=X_test.shape[0]//batch_size, callbacks=callbacks,#[hist],
                        epochs=TRAIN_EPOCHS)
    cpu_model = model.sync_to_cpu()
    json_string = cpu_model.to_json()
    open('/content/work/mymodel.json', 'w').write(json_string)

def find_good_epochs(train_epoch_list):
    result_list = []
    for epoch in train_epoch_list:
        K.clear_session()
        use_batch_norm = True
        if use_batch_norm:
            model = create_batch_norm_model()
        else:
            model = create_normal_model()

        # 元の係数を壊さないように低めの学習率を使う
        model.compile(tf.train.RMSPropOptimizer(4e-6), "binary_crossentropy", ["acc"])
        model.summary()

        tpu_grpc_url = "grpc://"+os.environ["COLAB_TPU_ADDR"]
        tpu_cluster_resolver = tf.contrib.cluster_resolver.TPUClusterResolver(tpu_grpc_url)
        strategy = keras_support.TPUDistributionStrategy(tpu_cluster_resolver)
        model = tf.contrib.tpu.keras_to_tpu_model(model, strategy=strategy)

        best_save_model_file = '/content/work/mymodel_maxEpoch' + str(epoch) + '.h5'
        history = History()
        callbacks = [
                     EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss',
                                   patience=20,
                                   verbose=1,
                                   min_delta=0.00001,
                                   mode='min'),
        #              ReduceLROnPlateau(monitor='val_loss',
        #                                factor=0.1,
        #                                patience=2,
        #                                verbose=1,
        #                                min_delta=0.0001,
        #                                mode='min'),
                     ModelCheckpoint(monitor='val_loss',save_weights_only=True,
                                     filepath=best_save_model_file,
                                     save_best_only=True,
                                     mode='min') ,
                     history,
                     ]


        batch_size = BATCH_SIZE

        model.fit_generator(generator(X_train, y_train, batch_size), steps_per_epoch=X_train.shape[0]//batch_size,
                            validation_data=generator(X_test, y_test, batch_size), 
                            validation_steps=X_test.shape[0]//batch_size, callbacks=callbacks,#[hist],
                            epochs=epoch)
        cpu_model = model.sync_to_cpu()
        precision, recall = check_results(cpu_model)
        print('precision : ' + str(precision))
        print('recall : ' + str(recall))
        result_list.append([best_save_model_file, precision])
    df = pd.DataFrame(result_list, columns=['weights', 'precision'])
    return df
